Currently this is set to the start frame.

You can mask your subject from any frame - be it a start, middle or end frame.

Currently Preview Bridge is not working. So for Inpainting we need to use an alternative solution.

Until it comes back, following manual solution works great:

1. Right click on the Preview Image and click on Copy Image
2. Select the Load Image Node and CTRL + V to paste the image.
3. On that, you can Inpaint, and it even saves the Mask inbetween sessions!
Save Video - This is helpful, if you have adjusted the frame_load_cap or the skip_first_frames values in the load video node. Disable this node, if you don't need that.
Run this node by selecting it first and pressing on  in the options above the node to on only "Execute to the selected output node".

Attention: A free Hugging Face account is required. You must also accept the models terms before downloading.
You can do this here: https://huggingface.co/facebook/sam3

Approval may take some time. After approval, we recommend creating a Hugging Face User Access Token and pasting it into the node int the hf_token attribute, as this is the fastest and most stable way to download the model on Runpod.
